text: Zbyszko is an old Polish name of Slavic origin, derived from diminutive form of names e.g. Zbigniew, Zbysław, Zbylut, etc. Notable people with the name include: *Stanislaus Zbyszko, strongman and professional wrestler prominent in the United States during the 1920s *Larry Zbyszko, professional wrestler known for his feud with wrestling legend Bruno Sammartino *Wladek Zbyszko, professional wrestler and strongman, brother of Stanislaus Zbyszko ==See also== *Zbigniew *Zbylut (given name) Category:Polish masculine given names Category:Slavic masculine given names Category:Masculine given names
title: Zbyszko
